reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute and Surprisingly Helpful
reviews.reviewText: When I first saw these sorts of indicators I rolled my eyes because how hard can it be to look in the dishwasher and see what the dish status is?And then I got married. And had a baby. Who is now a toddler.Let me tell you something, the number of times my husband and I have had to ask each other if the dishes in the washer were clean or not is probably normal.The number of times I haven't been able to remember after loading them myself is probably reason to call my doctor.All kidding aside, it really does help keep everyone straight about where we are in the dish cycle. Provided you remember to move the tab each time. I'll probably forget to do that, but that's on me.It is super cute and honestly the most helpful thing isn't the wording but the colors. I can look at it from across the room and see it without reading. It's a little thing but I was surprised at how useful that feature has been.As far as the product itself, it seems to be made of pretty cheap plastic. My two year old grabbed it on day one and it came apart. Luckily it all just snapped back together with no broken pieces but that was a little concerning. Since then he has left it alone, but if your littles can't keep their hands off of it, it might not hold up as well.The magnet seems strong. He only pulled the plastic window off of the front but couldn't pry the magnet up. It's not so strong to where it's a permanent fixture. I can scoot it around the dishwasher and relocate it easily, but I do think I'd have to actually work a little to completely remove it.Overall I'm happy with it. It's just one of those little things that makes life go a bit smoother, and in that case I'm all for it. Now if someone can just get my brain to remember to switch it with each load, that'd be great!
